{
  "texts": [
    "IntroductionThe World Health organisation (WHO) 1 reports that over 5% of people worldwide face disabling hearing loss, a number projected to rise to over 700 million by 2050.",
    "In Australia, the statistics reflect a similar concern.",
    "According to a report by the Hearing Care Industry Association (HCIA), 2 one in six individuals is affected by hearing loss, a number that is expected to rise to one in four by the year 2050.",
    "The aftermath of COVID is expected to worsen these statistics further [1].",
    "Such growth exacerbates communication challenges between deaf and hearing individuals, particularly in families with children settings.For the deaf and hearing loss communities, sign languages are their primary means of communication, whereas people with hearing mainly use spoken languages."
  ]
}